### Grafida Joomla Web Services read requests
###
### In PhpStorm, select the `local` environment and replace apiRoot and
### apiToken in http-client.env.json.
###
### Grafida sends both authentication headers. Joomla accepts either one on
### supported versions, but retaining both here mirrors ApiClient exactly.

### Shared request headers
# Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
# X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
# Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### Discover API base — alternate /api/index.php URL
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/index.php/v1/users/levels
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### Discover API base — rewrite-only URL
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/users/levels
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### List remote articles (Grafida defaults: first page, newest Joomla ID first)
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/content/articles?page[limit]=20&page[offset]=0&list[ordering]=a.id&list[direction]=desc
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### List remote articles with every Grafida-supported filter
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/content/articles?page[limit]=20&page[offset]=0&list[ordering]=a.title&list[direction]=asc&filter[search]=example&filter[category]=2&filter[tag]=3&filter[language]=en-GB&filter[state]=1&filter[featured]=1&filter[checked_out]=0
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### Fetch one remote article, including JSON:API category and tag relationships
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/content/articles/{{articleId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### List Joomla content categories
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/content/categories?filter[extension]=com_content&page[limit]=0
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### List tags
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/tags?page[limit]=0
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### List access levels
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/users/levels?page[limit]=0
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### List installed content languages
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/languages/content?page[limit]=0
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### List article custom fields
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/fields/content/articles?page[limit]=0
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### List site template styles (used to discover the active editor CSS)
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/templates/styles/site?page[limit]=0
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### Read Global Configuration entries (Grafida reads only `unicodeslugs`)
### Requires core.admin; do not save or expose the complete response.
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/config/application?page[offset]=0&page[limit]=500
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### List Media Manager adapters
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/media/adapters
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### Browse the default Media Manager root
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/media/files?url=1
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### Browse a Media Manager adapter path
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/media/files?url=1&path=local-images:/
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json

### Fetch one Media Manager file, including base64 content for the image editor
### Keep / and : literal in mediaPath; encode other special path characters.
GET {{apiRoot}}/api/v1/media/files/{{mediaPath}}?url=1&content=1
Authorization: Bearer {{apiToken}}
X-Joomla-Token: {{apiToken}}
Accept: application/vnd.api+json
